# Force all source / config text files to be stored and worked on as UTF-8.
#
# Why: 2026-05-11 we shipped a 315-line repair across 15 source files
# because a prior Windows-editor save had re-encoded JS template-string
# Unicode characters (emoji, middle-dot, arrows) as Latin-1/CP1252
# representations of UTF-8 bytes. The daily-report WhatsApp message
# then rendered as `ðŸ›ï¸ Beit Hady Â· Daily Performance` instead of
# `🏛️ Beit Hady · Daily Performance`. See commit 0b84ebf.
#
# `working-tree-encoding=UTF-8` tells Git to refuse to silently re-encode
# matching files on checkout/checkin. Combined with the pre-commit hook
# at `scripts/hooks/pre-commit` (auto-installed via `npm install`), this
# catches the mojibake class of corruption before it ships.

*.ts        text eol=lf working-tree-encoding=UTF-8
*.tsx       text eol=lf working-tree-encoding=UTF-8
*.js        text eol=lf working-tree-encoding=UTF-8
*.jsx       text eol=lf working-tree-encoding=UTF-8
*.mjs       text eol=lf working-tree-encoding=UTF-8
*.cjs       text eol=lf working-tree-encoding=UTF-8
*.json      text eol=lf working-tree-encoding=UTF-8
*.md        text eol=lf working-tree-encoding=UTF-8
*.sql       text eol=lf working-tree-encoding=UTF-8
*.html      text eol=lf working-tree-encoding=UTF-8
*.css       text eol=lf working-tree-encoding=UTF-8
*.yml       text eol=lf working-tree-encoding=UTF-8
*.yaml      text eol=lf working-tree-encoding=UTF-8

# Binary assets — never auto-convert.
*.pdf       binary
*.png       binary
*.jpg       binary
*.jpeg      binary
*.webp      binary
*.gif       binary
*.ico       binary
*.woff      binary
*.woff2     binary
*.zip       binary
*.xlsx      binary
*.xlsm      binary
